**LOGIC:**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/him431/image_1579014954.png)


 **For a/b,
  1) We check like b,2b,4b,8b ,.. max value that can be subtracted from a
  2) Subtract from a , add 2^x in result and continue**

```
class Solution {
    public int divide(int dividend, int divisor) {

        //Base Cases
        if (divisor == 1) {
            return dividend;
        }
        if (dividend == Integer.MIN_VALUE && divisor == -1) {
            return Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        }


        int result = 0;
        int a = dividend<0 ? -dividend : dividend;
        int b = divisor<0 ? -divisor : divisor;

        while(a-b>=0){
            int x=0;//by default start with : a-b*(2^0) = a-b
            while(a-(b<<x) >=0){ // a- b*(2^x) >= 0 , to get max x for this
                x++;
            }
            x--; // bcoz loop condition was not satisfied after last x++

            result += 1<<x; // count how many times b was added to itself i.e. 2^x
            a-= b<<x;       // subtract that max subtractable i.e. b*(2^x) from a
        }

        return (dividend >= 0) == (divisor >= 0) ? result : -result;
    }
}
```

