__Method 1:
Time Complexity : O(Dividend / Divisor) 
Naive Method to get the solution, 
Gives TLE therefore it has to be optimised__

```
class Solution
{ // There is Reason why this questioh has so low accuracy
public:
    int divide(int dividend, int divisor)
    {
        int sgn = ((dividend < 0) ^ (divisor < 0));
        long long int d = abs(dividend), dv = abs(divisor), ans = 0;
        if (dv == 1)
            ans = d;
        else
            while (d >= dv)        //Exhaustive subtraction
            {
                ++ans;
                d -= dv;
            }
        if (sgn == 1)
            ans = -ans;
        return ((ans < INT_MIN) ? INT_MIN : ((ans > INT_MAX) ? INT_MAX : ans ));
    }
};
```

__Now the task is to optimise the time-complexity, using bit-manipulation__

>__The idea here is to understand that any number can be represented
as sum of powers of 2__
>>__Check for the sign of the quotient
int sign = (divisor < 0) ^ (divendend < 0);
//if only one of them is negative, sign = 1, else 0__

>>__Pseudo Code
for i = 31 to i = 0,  since the question assumes that the number is 32 bit__
>>>  __So check till (divisor << i)  <= dividend,    
>>>   i.e.  [ divisor * (2 ^ i) ]    <=  dividend 
>>>   if true, add the power of 2 to the answer, and substract (divisor << i) from dividend
>>>   ans += 1 << i, i.e ans = ans + 2^i (power of 2)
>>>   dividend -= divisor << i__

>>__if sign = 1
ans = -ans;           //the quotient will be negative__

>>__Now that we have to give the answer in the required constraints
if ans > INT_MAX ( 2^31 -1), return INT_MAX, min(ans, INT_MAX )
if ans < INT_MIN (-2^31), return INT_MIN, max(INT_MIN, ans )__


__Below is the coding implementation
Method 2:
Time Complexity : O(31) ~ O(1)__

```
class Solution
{
public:
    int divide(int dividend, int divisor)
    {
        ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);    //Speed Game
        cin.tie(0);
        int sgn = (dividend < 0) ^ (divisor < 0);     //Get the sign of the quotient 
        long long int d = abs(dividend), dv = abs(divisor), ans = 0;   //Since left shift works only on positives, take absolute value
        for (int i = 31; i >= 0; i--)             //Explore all the 32 bits
            if (dv << i <= d)                     //If divisor * 2^i   <= dividend
            {
                ans += 1LL << i;                  //1LL prevents 2^31, to be treated as negative
                d -= dv << i;                      //Reduce the dividend
            }
        if (sgn == 1) // Number is negative
            ans = -ans;
        return ((ans < INT_MIN) ? INT_MIN : ((ans > INT_MAX) ? INT_MAX : ans ));
    }
};
```

