Dividing b/a means number of times we can remove a from b 
b - a -a - a- a- a ............k time
b - k*a

Instead of removing a one by one , we can remove it in groups. How?
any number k , can be written in the form of 2's powers. So the algorithm will be:
We solve the problem for positive dividend and divisior only and then decide the sign
1. Iterate from i=31 to 0, and try to remove the biggestpower * divisor
2. If it is removable, add it to the quotient and remove from dividend . Here adding and | is same as adding 2's powers will give same ans as using or operator in binary
3. Use long long as during multiplication the values may overflow
4. In the end check the limits specified by the question.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int divide(int x, int y) {
        int sign = ((x<0)^(y<0))?-1:+1;
        long long dividend = x, divisor=y,q=0;
        dividend=abs(dividend), divisor = abs(divisor);
        for(int i=31;i>=0;i--){
            if((divisor<<i) > dividend) continue;  
            q |= (1LL<<i);
            dividend -=  (divisor<<i);
        }
        q*=sign;
        if(q<0 and q<INT_MIN) q=INT_MIN;
        if(q>0 and q>INT_MAX) q=INT_MAX;
        return q;
    }
};
```

