solutions.content:
Based on Moore's voting algorithm to find majority element.
> There can be max two elements with count > n/3 ( n/3 + n/3 + n/3 = n ).

Initialize two majority elements with votes 0.
Loop through the array and
- Increase thier vote if it matches majority elements.
- Decrease otherwise.
- Reset the vote and majority element if the vote reaches zero.

At the end verify weather the majority elements indeed have count > n/3. If so then return it.

```C++
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> majorityElement( vector<int>& nums ) {
        // since we are looking for majority with more than n/3 votes
        // we can have only two majority element at max.

        // use moore's voting algorithm to get suspected majority1 and majority2
        int majority1 = INT_MAX, majority2 = INT_MAX;
        int votes1 = 0, votes2 = 0;
        for( auto num : nums ) {
            if( num == majority1 ) {
                votes1++;
            } else if ( num == majority2 ) {
                votes2++;
            } else if( votes1 == 0 ) {
                majority1 = num;
                votes1 = 1;
            } else if( votes2 == 0 ) {
                majority2 = num;
                votes2 = 1;
            } else {
