solutions.content:
To solve this in linear time and O(1) we will have to use Boyer Moore Voting algorithm. We will modify the algorithm to find two candidates. Since it is not possible to have more than 2 candidate elements that appear (n/3 + 1) times (because for 3 such elements 3*(n/3 + 1) = n + 3) we will have two variables to track our candidates.

Validation is required because in case where there are no such elements the algorithm can return any random element.
```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> majorityElement(int[] nums) {
        // https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boyer%E2%80%93Moore_majority_vote_algorithm
        // Since there can be at max two elements with atleast n/3 + 1 appearence
        // we will use Bayer Moore Voting algo to track two elements and verify them
        // at the end with a second pass


        int candidate1 = 0;
        int candidate2 = 0;
        int count1 = 0;
        int count2 = 0;

        for(int num : nums){
            if(num == candidate1){ // if our current candidate1 is found again then increase it's count
                count1++;
            }else if(num == candidate2){ // if our current candidate2 is found again then increase it's count
                count2++;
            }else if(count1 == 0){ // if our count1 is 0 it means we do not have a candidate1 so we start agains with current element
                candidate1 = num;
                count1++;
            }else if(count2 == 0){ // if our count2 is 0 it means we do not have a candidate2 so we start agains with current element
                candidate2 = num;
                count2++;
            }else{ // if our count1 and count2 is not 0 and the current element is neither equal to candidate1 or candidate2 we decrease counter of both candidates
                count1--;
                count2--;
            }
        }
        // If a solution does not exist then it is possible that Boyer Moore algo
        // returned just a random element so we have to verify our candidates
        // Now let's verify the two candidates are found atleast n/3 + 1 times
        count1 = 0;
        count2 = 0;
        for(int num : nums){
            if(num == candidate1){
                count1++;
            }else if(num == candidate2){
                count2++;
            }
        }

