solutions.content:
**Solution 1: Boyer–Moore majority vote algorithm**

Time complexity: `O(n)`
Space complexity: `O(1)`

```
class Solution 
{
    public List<Integer> majorityElement(int[] A)
    {
        List<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
        int major1 = 0, major2 = 0, count1 = 0, count2 = 0;

        for(int n : A)
        {
            if(major1 == n)
            {
                count1++;
            }
            else if(major2 == n)
            {
                count2++;
            }
            else if(count1 == 0)
            {
                major1 = n;
                count1 = 1;
            }
            else if(count2 == 0)
            {
                major2 = n;
                count2 = 1;
            }
            else
            {
                count1--;
                count2--;
            }    
        }
        count1 = 0;
        count2 = 0;

        for(int n : A)
        {
            if(n == major1)
                count1++;
            else if(n == major2)
                count2++;
        }
        if(count1 > A.length / 3) list.add(major1); 
        if(count2 > A.length / 3) list.add(major2);

        return list;
    }
}
```

**Solution 2: Using Hash-Table**

Time complexity: `O(n)`
Space complexity: `O(n)`

```
class Solution 
{
    public List<Integer> majorityElement(int[] A)
    {
        List<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        Set<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();

        for(int n : A)
        {
            map.put(n, map.getOrDefault(n, 0) + 1);
        }

        for(int n : A)
        {
            if(map.get(n) > A.length / 3)
                set.add(n);
        }
        list.addAll(set);
        return list;
    }
}
```

