solutions.content:
In a generic DFS problem, we look for a starting point and from there we look for an end target position to reach. 

`How is this question different than other DFS based problems ?`

In this, from a current cell we have to go in each direction and look for the maximum path length from all the possible directions we could go, right !

# The template : 
Here is the basic template that I use for solving the DFS problems : 
```
Basic DFS Template : 
1. Check when to apply DFS ( i.e. the valid position(/s) to start )
2. Writing dfs() : 
		a. base condition (`checking through isSafe()`)
		b. main logic ( `traverse to all possible directions, if it isSafe `)

Now, writing isSafe function could be a bit tricky but I will try to make it simple.
`At each step ( cell ) ask whether the current cell will help you to go ahead in dfs )` and based on this, the isSafe() would be implemented.

```
For example : 

The question : 
https://leetcode.com/problems/flood-fill/

The code : 
```
class Solution {
    public int[][] floodFill(int[][] image, int sr, int sc, int newColor) {
        if(image == null || image.length == 0) return image;
        int rows = image.length;
        int cols = image[0].length;

        if(image[sr][sc] == newColor) return image;

		// Step1 : CHECK WHEN TO APPLY DFS
        dfs(image, sr, sc, image[sr][sc], newColor, rows, cols);

        return image;
    }
    private void dfs(int[][] image, int i, int j, int val, int newColor, int rows, int cols) {

        boolean isCurrentCellSafe = isSafe(image, i, j, val, rows, cols);

        if(isCurrentCellSafe) {
            image[i][j] = newColor;
            dfs(image, i+1, j, val, newColor, rows, cols);
            dfs(image, i-1, j, val, newColor, rows, cols);
            dfs(image, i, j+1, val, newColor, rows, cols);
            dfs(image, i, j-1, val, newColor, rows, cols);
        }
    } 
	// isSafe()
    private boolean isSafe(int[][] image, int i, int j, int val, int rows, int cols) {
        if(i>=0 && i<rows && j>=0 && j<cols && image[i][j] == val) return true;
        return false;
    }
}
```


For the current question, the code is a bit different as I mentioned above. 
Also, we could remove the dp/memoized part for the time-being (` but it will give TLE` ) that is the basic reason I added the memoized code. ( and frankly speaking, this is the first question where I had to use memoization ) 

**What's so different about this question though ?**

Its important to mention that for most of dfs questions we do not add memoization upon a DFS. Normally when we could move to 4 directions, there would be cycle so we could not memoize the result. However since this question is strictly increasing, thus it is a DAG.


TC : `O(n * m)`
SC : `O(n * m)` 

****
```

class Solution {
    public int longestIncreasingPath(int[][] matrix) {
        if(matrix == null || matrix.length == 0) return 0;

        int rows = matrix.length;
        int cols = matrix[0].length;
        int maxLength = 0;

		// memoization
        int[][]dp = new int[rows+1][cols+1];
        for(int[] row : dp) {
            Arrays.fill(row, -1);
        }

		// check when to apply DFS
        for(int i=0;i<rows;i++) {
            for(int j=0;j<cols;j++) {
                maxLength = Math.max(maxLength, dfs(matrix, dp, i, j, rows, cols, Integer.MIN_VALUE));
            }
        }

        return maxLength;
    }
    private int dfs(int[][] matrix, int[][]dp, int i, int j, int rows, int cols, int compareWith) {

        boolean isCurrentCellSafe = isSafe(matrix, i, j, compareWith);

        int result = 0;

        if(isCurrentCellSafe) {

            if(dp[i][j] != -1) return dp[i][j];

            int ch = matrix[i][j];
            matrix[i][j] = -1;

            // Go in each direction, and check which path yields the maximum length path
            // This is giving TLE, so we will have to memoize the code

            int d = dfs(matrix, dp, i+1, j, rows, cols, ch) ;
            int u = dfs(matrix, dp, i-1, j, rows, cols, ch) ;
            int r = dfs(matrix, dp, i, j+1, rows, cols, ch) ;
            int l = dfs(matrix, dp, i, j-1, rows, cols, ch) ;

            // adding 1, to include the current cell in the path

            result = 1 + Math.max(Math.max(d,u), Math.max(l,r));
            matrix[i][j] = ch;

            dp[i][j] = result;
        }
        return result;
    }
    private boolean isSafe(int[][]matrix, int i, int j, int cw) {
        if(i>=0 && i<matrix.length && j>=0 && j<matrix[0].length && matrix[i][j] > cw && cw!=-1) {
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```


Hope this helps you with the basic idea of solving the DFS based questions. 

In general, this is the DFS template that would work in most/many questions with slight modifications.

