# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
It can be solved by using Simple DFS Algorithm.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Choose every element of the matrix as a starting point and apply the DFS algorithm in which we check the maximum possible length of the increasing path through a particular starting point, now we take the the maximum of the all possible paths. This might give a TLE . SO, SIMPLE MEMOIZATION CAN BE DONE FOR THE SAME CODE!! 
# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(N*M)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
- Space complexity: $$O(N*M)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


