We can model this problem as a graph in which each cell is a vertex. An edge exists only from node `u` to node `v` if `u` and `v` are adjacent up/down/left/right neighbors in `matrix` and if `matrix[u] < matrix[v]` - this is because we are looking to model only increasing paths per problem statement. 

model matrix as a graph (defaultdict of sets)

`adj_to = {u1 : {v1, v2, v3}}`

compute indegrees of all vertices in a defaultdict of ints

`indegree = {v1: 1, v2: 2}`

perform standard topological sort of graph, keeping track of the max possible depth we can reach.

for topological sort we start with all vertices of 0 indegree
we visit those vertices and decrement their adjacent neighbors' indegrees by 1
if any of those are now 0, add them to our `to_visit` queue
we also keep track of the depth reached on the queue

 ```
 def longestIncreasingPath(self, matrix: List[List[int]]) -> int:

        adj_to = collections.defaultdict(set)
        indegree = collections.defaultdict(int)

        for i, row in enumerate(matrix):
            for j, cell in enumerate(row):
                if i > 0 and cell < matrix[i-1][j]:
                    adj_to[(i,j)] |= {(i-1,j)}
                    indegree[(i-1,j)] += 1
                if j > 0 and cell < matrix[i][j-1]:
                    adj_to[(i,j)] |= {(i,j-1)}
                    indegree[(i,j-1)] += 1
                if i < len(matrix)-1 and cell < matrix[i+1][j]:
                    adj_to[(i,j)] |= {(i+1,j)}
                    indegree[(i+1,j)] += 1
                if j < len(row)-1 and cell < matrix[i][j+1]:
                    adj_to[(i,j)] |= {(i,j+1)}
                    indegree[(i,j+1)] += 1

        to_visit = collections.deque()

        [to_visit.append(((i,j),1)) 
         for i in range(len(matrix)) 
         for j in range(len(matrix[i])) 
         if not indegree[(i,j)]]

        max_depth = 0

        while to_visit:

            cur, depth = to_visit.popleft()
            max_depth = max(max_depth, depth)
            for adj in adj_to[cur]:
                indegree[adj] -= 1
                if not indegree[adj]:
                    to_visit.append((adj,depth+1))

        return max_depth
```

